From 5bbe5e4bd7fb5980e69b9f116f85c91f864592e0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Prajw <prajw@trivartatech>
Date: Sun, 26 Apr 2026 21:41:10 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] feat: useFormat composable + sweep date displays to honour
 System Config
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds resources/js/Composables/useFormat.js — a shared Vue composable
that reads the school's date_format / time_format from the Inertia
shared props (school.settings) and exposes:
  formatDate(d), formatTime(t), formatDateTime(dt), formatMoney(n)

Falls back gracefully:
  - empty / null  → '—'
  - invalid Date  → passthrough (server-formatted strings render as-is)
  - missing settings → DD/MM/YYYY default

Replaced the per-page hardcoded en-IN formatters in 21 admin pages so
they now honour whatever the admin sets in
School Settings → System Config → Date Format / Time Format. Touched:

  Alumni/Index, Disciplinary/Index, Fee/StructureHistory,
  Hostel/GatePasses/StudentPortal, Houses/Show,
  Inventory/{Index,Reports,Show}, Library/Issues,
  PTM/{Index,SessionDetail}, Quiz/{Index,MyQuizzes,Results},
  Staff/{History,HistoryLog,Punch}, Setup/RolloverWizard,
  Transport/Attendance/Report,
  Examinations/{MarkSummary,Results}/Print

Decorative inline calls (e.g. extracting just the weekday short name
or month abbreviation in calendar headers) were left alone — those
aren't full-date displays and the System Config doesn't have a
single-component format equivalent.

Documentation examples in Settings/NumberFormats.vue and Fee/Config.vue
deliberately left alone — they showcase format tokens like {MON} and
need a sample date independent of the user's system config.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
